description:
Year of the Tsar 2674 AD, and the bastard son of the Romanov's, Nikolai Dante, has bonded with a cyberorganic Weapons Crest, an alien combat computer, which allows him to extrude lethal bio-blades. Following the civil war, Tsar Vladimir the Conqueror is strengthening his control over Imperial Russia, and he's appointed Dante as his troubleshooter! 
 
Collecting the Nikolai Dante stories from 2000 AD:

The Road of Bones from 2000 AD Prog 2007 originally published in 2006 
Deadlier than the Male from 2000 AD progs #1518-1520 originally published in 2007

description: Year of the Tsar 2676 AD. The bastard son of the Romanovs, Nikolai Dante, leads a rebellion against Vladimir the Conqueror. Supported by the tyrant's daughter, Jena Makarov, his mother - pirate queen Katarina Dante - and some of his weapons-crest-enabled siblings, can Dante finally bring down Vladimir? And if so, can he bring peace to the empire, or is there someone else vying for power?
name: Hero of the Revolution

description: No one knows why dragons appear; their very presence bends reality out of shape. This influence destroys everything, transforms men and beasts into monsters: it is the Veill. Only virgins are free of this scourge and can approach the beast to kill it. This is why the Order of the Dragon Knights was created.
name: Jaïna

description:
NO ONE KNOWS WHY DRAGONS APPEAR...

Their very presence bends reality out of shape. This influence destroys everything, transforms men and beasts into monsters: it is the Veill. Only virgins are free of this scourge and can approach the beast to kill it. This is why the Order of the Dragon Knights was created.
name: Akanah

description:
THE DRAGON KNIGHTS MUST FACE UP TO THEIR CONTRADICTIONS…

BUT WHAT IF THEIR DESTINY WAS NOT JUST TO FIGHT THE VEILL?

When a dragon is roused from its slumbers in the heart of a volcano, the City built on its slopes, refuse to believe in the Veill’s existence and hinder Tyra and the Dragon Knights who have come to their aide…

The Dragon Knights are moved to pity by the plight of the slaves. But what is the Dragon Knights’ duty? To combat the Beast or change the world?
name: Revoir le soleil

description:
INTERTWINING QUESTS IN A NEW STORY

Three dragon-knights wake up in pitch darkness.They lie bound and gagged on the fl oor of a cell, in an unknown place with no windows on the outside world.Who brought them here? And how?And above all, why…?
name: Aveugles

description:
ALONE IN THE MIDDLE OF THE DESERT, THEY MUST SURVIVE…

Three Red Wings, the flying ships of The Dragon Knight Order fight a dragon in the skies. The monster hits a plane that crashes in the middle of the desert in the middle of the Veill. Among the survivors, apprentices of the Order, a mother with her child, a young man with a mysterious past and the ship’s second in command. They must survive, cross these dry grounds. The dragon that haunts the desert could be the lesser evil…
name: Vers la lumière

description:
Prince of Persia: Before the Sandstorm -- A 120-page graphic novel prequel based upon the upcoming Walt Disney Film, Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time

Written by Jordan Mechner, the creator of Prince of Persia, this gorgeously illustrated graphic anthology will appeal to fans of the video game franchise, fans of the movie, and fans of comics and graphic novels! Dive further into the world of the upcoming Walt Disney Film, Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time with this book of six original stories, all highlighting the characters and the world of the film, with art by some of the best and brightest talents in comics!
name: Before The Sandstorm

volume.name: Prince of Persia: Before the Sandstorm

description:
In the dystopian Zürich of 2032, an economic crisis that happened in 2012, the richer got richer and the poorer became so poor that they were forced to build their new homes in shanty-towns at the bottom of a dried out Lake Zurich. Journalist Finn Meyer one night happens upon a group of thugs beating up an old man. It is then that he witnesses a man, dressed like Willhelm Tell - Swiss National Hero - who saves the old man by shooting them with his crossbow and savagely beating them up. Meyer decides to investigate the mysterious vigilante, who apparently possesses superhuman strength, the other media have dubbed a "creature", but gets caught up in a conspiracy of policits, religion and economy. And when a person calling himself Gessler - in Swiss folklore, he was the enemy of Tell - shows up on a glider, seemingly possessing electric powers, Meyer decides to investigate the origins of both Tell and Gessler.

Publication History

As every book by Swiss publisher Zampano, Tell was first published as a webcomic. When the first arc was finished, it was collected and published as a trade paperback in November of 2010.
name: Die Legende Kehrt Zurück

description:
Finally in London, Clint and Selena find themselves driven apart by a secret from Selena’s past. And as the so-called “peace” created by the military slips away, one question will rise from the ashes: are the Clint and Selena more powerful together…or apart? If you loved the 28 DAYS LATER movies, this is the comic book you should be reading!

While Selena is reconnecting with her past, trying to find closure, Clint is still in the refugee camp, trying to survive. However, with the Rage Virus loose in the camp, this quickly becomes a difficult task. And when the army decides to take even more drastic measures, it becomes nearly impossible.

Prepare yourself for an exploration into the past of one of Batman's greatest foes! In this tale collecting the 2-part Prestige Format miniseries, Ra's al Ghul has left a world filled with reanimated corpses. To save Gotham, Batman must uncover al Ghul's centuries of secret world travels!
name: Year One: Batman/Ra's Al Ghul

description: The tale of Wynonna Earp during the Yeti Wars is brought to the comics page in this four-part series by master storyteller and Wynonna Earp creator Beau Smith, with art and cover by Enrique Villigran.

After being threatened by a group of hooded men, the Dungeon Keeper sends for the great barbarian hero Ababakar Octopuce to track down and slay said offenders. Unfortunately, Herbert, a lowly employee of the dungeon, ends up accidentally killing the famed barbarian, and out of fear of punishment assumes his identity. If that wasn't enough, Herbert become's the unwilling owner of the Sword of Destiny, which denies Herbert it's use until he proves himself worthy, but also forbids him the use of any other weapon.
name: Cœur de canard

description: Due to his failure to stop the giantess Sonia, Herbert is sent on a quest to improve his fighting skills. Marvin tries to help Herbert by introducing him to his old mentor. The old master's methods however turn out to be questionable at best.
name: Le roi de la bagarre

description:
In order to attract more adventurers into his dungeon, the Dungeon Keeper sends out Herbert and Marvin to spread the rumor that a princess is being held captive behind it's walls. The plan proves a success, as legions of adventurers crowd the dungeon's corridors. 
Little do they know that the rebellious barbarian princess Isis has chosen the dungeon as her new hiding place. 
And her  father Attaman is looking for her.
name: La Princesse des barbares

description:
The preparations for the wedding of the Dungeon Master and princess Isis are almost complete.  Marvin as the wedding planner has sworn with his life to make sure everything goes perfect. 
The Dungeon Master however has other plans. He secretly instructs Herbert and Isis to run-off together, so that he can receive compensation from the Ataman. 
The pair's plans to escape are however overheard by Marvin, and he won't have anyone betray his master, even if they claim it was his idea.
name: Un mariage à part

description:
As part of the preparations for the arranged marriage between princess Isis and the Dungeon Keeper, Herbert, Marvin,  Alcibiabe, and Isis head out to the market. 

Things go smoothly until Alcibiabe is tricked by a conman. 
Meanwhile, the ever loyal Marvin becomes suspicious of the friendly behavior Herbert and Isis are displaying for each other.
name: Sortilèges et avatars

description:
An actual secret war for power is happening in the backstages of the financial groups. One of the most used assault techniques is the Tender Offer, a type of public takeover bid.

The W Group launches, as a counter-attack, a Tender Offer on the Fenico, a conglomerate of companies managed by the nice yet cunning Gus Fenimore.
name: O.P.A.
Les trois yeux des gardiens du Tao
Masquerade

description: Nothing will ever be the same again, and this time we mean it! Not even Captain America can escape the sins buried in his past, and Bucky Barnes’ future hangs in the balance as evidence of the Winter Soldier’s crimes comes to light. And with Bucky’s trial distracting our heroes, the new Red Skull plots a terror attack at the heart of America! Plus: Steve Rogers emerged from the Super-Soldier Program to become the first Captain America, the Sentinel of Liberty. When he died, Bucky Barnes took up the shield to become a new kind of Captain America. With Barnes on trial, who will wield the legendary weapon? Who will become the new Captain of America? It’s the start of a new era for the famed Avenger! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA #611-615 and #615.1, and material from CAPTAIN AMERICA 70TH ANNIVERSARY MAGAZINE.
name: Captain America: The Trial of Captain America

volume.name: Captain America: The Trial of Captain America

description: Out of a world of mists, magic, sword and sorcery comes the ultimate Celtic warrior - Slaine. Exiled from his tribe, he is forced to roam the land of Tir-Nan-Og with his dwarf Ukko, on his quest to claim his rightful place as king.
name: The Collected Slaine

description:
Cover painted by Stephen Hickman with a back cover painted by fantasy art legend Michael Whelan, which was later used as a cover for issue #1

Harlan Ellison's Dream Corridor Special is the launchpad for Dark Horse Comics Dream Corridor series. All of the stories are adapted from the prose works of Harlan Ellison. This issue contains interstitial sequences written by Ellison and drawn by Eric Shanower, as well as a special prose story written by Ellison around the cover painting.

Story Titles

  • Quicktime by Wein and Broderick
  • The End Of The Time Of Leinard by Perozich and Wildey
  • Rat Hater by Perozich and Gilbert
  • If This Be Utopia by Foglio and Howarth
  • On The Slab by Perozich and Gianni
  • Midnight In The Sunken Cathedral part 1 (prose) by Ellison
name: Dream Corridor Special

description: Rare out of print sampler anthology.
name: Bumper KNOCKABOUT Trial Special

description: Think you know everything there is to know about the original X-Men? Think again! Something happened to Cyclops, Marvel Girl, Beast, Angel, Iceman and Professor X years ago, a secret so horrible that it has been locked away in the dark corner of Cyclops' mind until today. What crisis strikes in the present that calls upon memories of the past? Witness the astonishing debut of the Evolutionaries! Taking the lead for a few issues is famed X-Men writer CHRIS YOST (X-FORCE) and with all this danger, he’s lucky to have regular X-MEN artist PACO MEDINA and DALIBOR TALAJIC (PUNISHER) along for the ride.
name: First To Last, Part One

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Two-Face is back! As an unknown villain targets Two-Face and other Gotham City crimelords for extermination, Batman discovers that Kitrina Falcone, a.k.a. "CATGIRL," is next on the hit list! Can he save the junior mobster in time? And will helping Kitrina force Catwoman to get involved?
name: Pieces, Part One: Lost

description: They live among us: they can be our friends, our parents, our wife or husband, or even ourselves. They are monsters, disguised in a human mask. Dylan Dog knows that thet live an awful life, devoured by shame, loneliness, anger and thirst... for blood.
name: Vivono tra noi

description:
In a town where movie-star beauty is only a surgery away, it’s hard to tell what’s real...

A cosmetic surgeon takes pride in his best work: an ingénue of the silver screen, literally built for success. While he plans one last procedure to perfect her looks, his aging wife struggles to keep his interest, and his ambitious assistant threatens his practice with a disturbing new technique.

In his debut graphic novel, acclaimed mini-comic creator Will Dinski presents a haunting pastel vision of beauty, surgery, and jealousy, served with a sci-fi twist.
name: Fingerprints

description: A tale from Batman's past! The young Dark Knight has just begun his war on crime. But if he wants to prowl the shadows, Batman must first withstand the light of Gotham City's original protector: the Golden Age Green Lantern!
name: Shadows & Light

volume.name: The All-New Batman: The Brave and the Bold
